<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Domicile Certificate Application Process | DocAssist</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/aadhar.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header class="doc-header">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Domicile Certificate Documentation</h1>
            <p>Residential Proof Certificate - State Government</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
        <section class="doc-overview">
            <div class="card">
                <img src="/images/<%= data.image_data %>" alt="Domicile Certificate Sample" class="doc-logo">
                <div class="doc-meta">
                    <p><strong>Issuing Authority:</strong> Tahsildar/Revenue Department (State Government)</p>
                    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Educational admissions, government jobs, scholarships</p>
                    <p><strong>Validity:</strong> Typically lifetime (varies by state)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="application-process">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-list-ol"></i> Step-by-Step Application Process</h2>
            
            <div class="process-steps">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">1</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Check Eligibility</h3>
                        <p>Requirements vary by state but generally:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Must be resident of the state for 3-15 years (varies)</li>
                            <li>Age should be above 18 years (for independent applicants)</li>
                            <li>Parents' domicile can be used for minors</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">2</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Collect Required Documents</h3>
                        <p>Prepare original + photocopies of:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Address Proof:</strong> Aadhaar, Voter ID, Ration Card, Utility bills</li>
                            <li><strong>Age Proof:</strong> Birth certificate, School leaving certificate</li>
                            <li><strong>Residence Proof:</strong> Property documents/Rental agreement + Affidavit</li>
                            <li><strong>Passport-size photographs</strong> (2-4 copies)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">3</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Fill Application Form</h3>
                        <p>Obtain form from:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Tehsil office or District Magistrate office</li>
                            <li>State's e-District portal (e.g., <a href="https://edistrict.delhigovt.nic.in/" target="_blank">Delhi e-District</a>)</li>
                            <li>Provide personal details, residence duration, and purpose</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">4</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Submit Application</h3>
                        <p>Submission methods:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Offline:</strong> At Tehsil office with documents</li>
                            <li><strong>Online:</strong> Through state e-District portal with scanned copies</li>
                            <li>Pay applicable fees (₹20-200, varies by state)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">5</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Verification Process</h3>
                        <p>Authorities will:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Verify submitted documents</li>
                            <li>May conduct field visit to confirm residence</li>
                            <li>Check with local authorities (police/panchayat)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">6</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Receive Certificate</h3>
                        <p>Processing time:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Normal cases:</strong> 15-30 working days</li>
                            <li><strong>Online applications:</strong> May be faster in some states</li>
                            <li>Collect from office or download from portal (if applied online)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="video-guide">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-video"></i> Official Tutorial Video</h2>
            <div class="video-container">
                <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ptIf6-ZJ1d0" title="Domicile Certificate Application Process" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
            <p class="video-caption">Domicile certificate application process tutorial</p>
        </section>

        <section class="important-notes">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-exclamation-circle"></i> Important Information</h2>
            <div class="notes-grid">
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> State Variations</h3>
                    <p>Residence duration requirements vary:<br>
                    Delhi: 3 years<br>
                    UP: 5 years<br>
                    Maharashtra: 15 years</p>
                </div>
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-rupee-sign"></i> Fees</h3>
                    <p>₹20-50: Normal fee<br>
                    ₹100-200: Late applications<br>
                    Free for SC/ST in some states</p>
                </div>
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-users"></i> Special Cases</h3>
                    <p>Married women can use parents' or husband's domicile. Minors can use parents' domicile.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-phone-alt"></i> Helpline</h3>
                    <p>State e-District helplines<br>
                    Local Tehsil office contact<br>
                    Common helpline: <strong>1075</strong> (for some states)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-section">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Is domicile certificate same as residence certificate?</h3>
                <p>No, domicile certificate proves permanent residence while residence certificate proves current residence. Domicile has more legal weight.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Can I get domicile certificate if I'm living on rent?</h3>
                <p>Yes, with rental agreement + affidavit from landlord and utility bills in your name for required duration.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Is domicile certificate mandatory for college admissions?</h3>
                <p>Required for state quota seats in most government colleges and universities.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="doc-footer">
        <div class="container">
            <p>For state-specific information, visit your <a href="https://edistrict.gov.in/" target="_blank">state e-District portal</a></p>
            <p class="disclaimer">This information is provided for guidance only. DocAssist is not affiliated with any government body.</p>
        </div>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>